{"type":"message","id":"d0317e89","parentId":"da773d57","timestamp":"2026-03-19T09:11:38.090Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can read the MEMORY.md. Now I need to:\n\n1. Update MEMORY.md with current session context\n2. Create a new session via agentTurn\n\nActually, the issue is that the context-monitor.ps1 script just monitors and logs but doesn't trigger the automatic switch. According to the skill, there should be a seamless-switch mechanism that:\n1. Saves context to memory\n2. Creates a new session via agentTurn\n\nLet me create a more complete implementation. Since the current cron job just runs a script that checks and logs, I need to implement the actual session switch.\n\nLet me:\n1. First, save the current session context to memory (update MEMORY.md with recent context)\n2. Trigger a new isolated session that will load memory and continue\n\nActually, looking at the skill more carefully, the automatic switch should happen via the cron job. But the current implementation doesn't do that - it just logs a warning.\n\nI have two options:\n1. Manually trigger a new session with agentTurn\n2. Modify the context-monitor script to do the automatic switch\n\nSince this is the context monitor job running in isolation, I should:\n1. Update the memory with current context\n2. Trigger a new session to continue\n\nLet me first get the recent session history to understand what's been discussed, then save that to memory and trigger a new session.","thinkingSignature":"545d29c278da043a6d1e1dc44def08cf0af4613b4e9a18583d7cd3d94ef9984c"},{"type":"text","text":"现在让我获取当前会话历史，记录上下文，然后触发新会话：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_o5xc7sidscqi_1","name":"sessions_history","arguments":{"limit":20,"sessionKey":"agent:main:main"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.5","usage":{"input":8994,"output":333,"cacheRead":37011,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46338,"cost":{"input":0.0026982,"output":0.00039